<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-102-121  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 102 121.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 18 1990 n305 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Global-Mobile plan. (Motorola Inc. plans launch of satellitenetwork)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lynch, Karen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Motorola plans the launch of a global satellite communicationssystem.andP;  The system will provide mobile communications servicesbased on a network of 77 small satellites, or seven satellites ina total of 11 orbits.andP;  Motorola has already presented the idea forthe network to regulators and international telecommunicationsorganizations, and will formally announce the geostationary systemin late Jun 1990.andP;  The low orbit technology provides for placementof the satellites at 375 miles above the earth rather than thestandard 23,437 mile orbits.andP;  Motorola will be facing competitionin the satellite arena, as two other firms, North American CLS andOrbital Science are also planning low orbit satellite networks.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (planning).andO;Ticker:    MOT.andO;Topic:     Business PlanningSatellite CommunicationsInternational CommunicationsCommunications Service SuppliersCompetition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>